data.description: Undeniably, this is the most coveted natural landscape in the heart of the Sonoran Desert & within 10 miles to the downtown Phoenix area. Thriving with high demand and strong property values, this pristine topographic canvas is being presented to market. Neighboring South Mountain Park/Preserve is over 16,000 acres, and one of the largest municipally managed parks in the nation consisting of three mountain ranges (Ma Ha Tauk, Gila and Guadalupe) which cradle the offered parcels providing protection from the elements and an enclave for serenity. Here, engage in outdoor activities to re-energize, and re-connect with the natural world while cultivating and preserving the resources for generations to come. With more than 50 miles of trails for hiking, horseback riding and mountain biking. With the scarcity of natural resources and proximity of these parcels located in the Metropolitan Phoenix Area, new 202 freeway, shopping, dining, and entertainment, the key holder for this offering possesses an omniscience to hold such a remarkable awareness of the past, present and future. This parcel is one of three which can be separated from the grouping. A development opportunity whether for an individual, investment group, or brilliant other seeking the breathtaking radiance only the natural world can provide to incorporate into a public or private offering is now available to own.
